fields.name: Korean Yew Bonsai
fields.description:
The yew is an evergreen dioecious (male and female flowers grow on separate trees ) 
shrub or tree with dark green needle-shaped foliage. The genus Taxus occurs 
in the temperate zones of the northern hemisphere. 
Although the yew is considered to be a conifer, it does not bear woody cones 
but produces seed cones with a single seed surrounded by a berry-like 
red aril which is open at the end.

fields.name: Hinoki Bonsai
fields.description:
Japanese Hinoki Bonsai is a slow-growing, evergreen tree native to Japan, valued for its fine-textured foliage, elegant form, and aromatic wood. It requires careful pruning, wiring, and soil management to thrive as a bonsai.

This plant is grown as bonsai and requires minimal pruning. A bright environment will be perfect for this centrepiece.

Potted in Sprout Handmade Bonsai Planter from South Korea

Dimensions:
Potted Plant: W 20-25 cm x H 20-25 cm

fields.name: Procumbens Nana Sonare Juniper
fields.description:
Procumbens nana Bonsai tree is a Japanese Juniper with a Thick Gnarly trunk
 Beautiful tree that is established and healthy, it is an 18 year old tree
 Loves to grow outside in full sun, but can be grown inside with lights or if you have a lot of sunlight , needs at least four hours direct sun daily.

fields.description:
Japanese White Pine ‘Negishi’, not to be confused with the more commonly known Japanese Black Pine, featuring beautiful silverish-blue short needles. 

The product image accurately represents the actual product.

fields.name: Bonsai Hedera
fields.description:
Korean Hedera, commonly known as Korean ivy, is a variegated evergreen vine with glossy, lobed leaves. It thrives in various conditions, clinging to surfaces with aerial roots, and adds lush greenery to landscapes.

Dimensions:
Potted Plant: W 5-10 cm x H 10-15 cm

fields.name: Stephania Kaweesakii ‘Nova’
fields.description:
The new leaves of Stephania Kaweesakii ‘Nova’ can appear purple or green and change to dark green as it matures. The size of a mature leaf can reach up to 20cm in diameter. 

Toxic to children and pets when ingested.

Plants images depicted are solely for illustration purposes only.

fields.name: Stephania Suberosa
fields.description: A caudiciform plant with light green vines and big leaves. This species of Stephania has an interesting cracked caudex. It is toxic to pets and humans when ingested.
